In a message dated 8/17/01 7:38:45 PM Pacific Daylight Time, rdahl@... 
writes:

<< OOC: Kslawdogg, a lot of wrestlers have come straight from Pro Football,
 the Rock is just one of many, and he stole the Rock Bottom from someone
 else in turn, barely any moves are made up nowadays, he just uses a
 Sambo Suplex, (or Orange Suplex? can't remember) I dislike the Rock, but
 he is good for the buisness, so I tolerate him, but you are way wrong
 when you say that WCW wrestlers have no character, the only WCW
 wrestlers that WWF got were the rookies, because Mchamahon is to cheap
 to buy the big names like Sting, Jarrett, and Steiner. Don't forget that
 Chris Benoit, Chris Jericho, Steven Regal, all learned their trade in
 the WCW. >>

The Rock didn't come straight from pro football though.  And so?  He uses a 
move that Owen Hart used to use as well.  He's got better moves than the WCW. 
 Jake the Snake used the DDT as his major move now it's used by everyone.  
Heh, Jeff Jarret is one of my least favorites, even when he was in the WWF 
Owen Hart carried him along.  Steiner, no idea who he is.  Sting was in the 
WWF before he was in the WCW by the way.  And I'd like to point out his look 
in the WCW is laughable compared to the look during his years in the WWF.  
You may not have read what I said earlier, but I said I thought Benoit 
sucked, and I also said the WCW and ECW were breeding grounds for wrestlers 
who can make it to the big time in the WWF.  Steven Regal's been in the WWF 
for a while, too.  Before Regal he was The Manly Man, can't remember his 
named but it was something The Manly Man.
